===Verb===
{{en-verb|abhor|r|ing}}

# {{context|transitive}} To regard with [[horror]] or [[detestation]]; to [[shrink]] back with [[shudder]]ing from; to feel excessive [[repugnance]] toward; to [[detest]] to extremity; to [[loathe]]. {{defdate|First attested from around (1350 to 1470).}}<ref name=SOED>{{reference-book | last =| first = | authorlink =  | coauthors =  | editor =Brown, Lesley  | others =  | title = The Shorter Oxford English Dictionary | origdate =  | origyear = 1933| origmonth =  | url =  | format =  | accessdate =  | accessyear =  | accessmonth =  | edition = 5th | date =  | year =2003| month =  | publisher =Oxford University Press  | location =Oxford, UK | language =  | id =  | doi = | isbn =978-0-19-860575-7 | lccn = | ol = | pages =4| chapter =  | chapterurl =  | quote =}}</ref>
